DURBAN - Three teenagers have been arrested in connection with the stabbing of a Gauteng youngster on Wednesday.
Mondeor High School Grade 11 pupil Khulani Mathebula, 19, was fatally stabbed while walking to school.

Gauteng police spokesperson Captain Kay Makhubele said two of the suspects, who are both 15 years old, were arrested in Soweto and Naturena yesterday morning.
The arrests come after a 13-year-old boy was arrested on Wednesday afternoon.
The National Prosecuting Authority’s Gauteng spokesperson, Phindi Louw Mjonondwane, tweeted that the 13-year-old was to appear in the juvenile court charged with murder and robbery with aggravating circumstances.

 
 
   Three teenagers have been arrested in connection with the stabbing of a Gauteng youngster on Wednesday. File photo.
 

Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi said: “It’s scenes like this, of parents mourning, that break my heart. I am tired of submitting death certificates instead of graduations.”
He said the department needed to review its safety systems at schools. 
- Mercury Correspondent and African News Agency (ANA)